Ramsey R(5,5) — Exhaustive Extension of ALL 656 K₄₂ Colorings
Date: 2026-03-30
Method: 4-SAT encoding (42 variables, ~2318 clauses per coloring)
Solver: Glucose3 (via python-sat)

RESULT: 0 / 656 colorings have valid extensions.
Time: 3.03 seconds (was estimated 3 hours via GPU brute force)

Key insight: the 2^42 extension search is a 4-SAT instance.
Each monochromatic K₄ in the base graph becomes one 4-clause.
SAT solvers handle this trivially — the problem is massively
overconstrained (~2318 constraints on 42 binary variables).

Expected solutions per coloring: 2^42 × (15/16)^2318 ≈ 10^{-50}

Conclusion: NONE of the 656 known (5,5)-good K₄₂ colorings
(McKay-Radziszowski database) can be extended to K₄₃.
This is the strongest computational evidence that R(5,5) = 43.

Note: This does NOT prove R(5,5) = 43. A K₄₃ coloring could
exist that is NOT an extension of any K₄₂ coloring in the database.
